n=E2=80=99s basketball teams practice. It was, simply, beautiful. Then I to=
ok in the football training facility, which was completed 20 years ago. The=
 building, which once weaned a young Mahomes, seemed nice enough to me, but=
 is outdated compared to those of rival schools. Naturally, the university =
is constructing a replacement next door.<br/><br/>For the past decade, univ=
ersities have viewed these souped-up, hyper-advanced athletics complexes as=
 a key factor in attracting recruits.
Unsurprisingly, of course, institutions of higher learning have wound up sp=
ending extraordinary oodles of money=E2=80=94counting on donors, boosters, =
and public funding=E2=80=94to build the most luxurious practice facilities =
around. Some of the most historic and bucolic campuses now look like nostal=
gic appendages to Martian-like modern athletic coliseums. So it goes=E2=80=
=A6<br/><br/>But starting right around the time that the Womble Center was =
erected, schools have discovered=E2=80=94<i>duh</i>=E2=80=94that recruits a=
re much more interested in Name, Image, and Likeness (N.I.L.) opportunities=
